.01
       
Indebtedness
.
 
The Company shall not, and shall not permit any of its Subsidiaries to, directly or indirectly, create, incur, assume or guaranty, or otherwise become or remain directly or indirectly liable with respect to, any Indebtedness, except:
 
(a)
          
Each Loan Party may become and remain liable with respect to the Obligations;
(b)
          
the Company and its Subsidiaries may become and remain liable with respect to Indebtedness in respect of Capital Leases in an aggregate amount not to exceed at any time $50,000,000;
 
(c)
          
the Company and its Subsidiaries may become and remain liable with respect to (i) purchase money Indebtedness and (ii) non-recourse Indebtedness and obligations of the Company and its Subsidiaries in connection with any Accounts Receivable Facility, collectively in an aggregate outstanding principal amount not to exceed $100,000,000 at any time;
 
(d)
          
the Foreign Subsidiaries of the Borrower may become and remain liable with respect to Indebtedness in an aggregate outstanding principal amount not to exceed $250,000,000 at any time; and
 
(e)
          
any other Indebtedness of the Company and its Subsidiaries, provided that, the incurrence of any such Indebtedness is not prohibited by .
